Simplify version extraction code

New scheme:
Use the distribution version if it exists. 
In case the distribution is not available or points to an installation 
in another filesystem location fall back to using `git describe`. 
The output will be reformatted as a PEP440 compatible 'local version' suffix.

Example: v0.0.1+git-3-g1234567-dirty

Use sub-data-directories in runmultiple

The `runmultiple` command now creates sub directories for each validator
node in `config['data_dir']`/<validator number>, instead of cluttering the
CWD with new directories.

This allows to actually control the data-dir path with the `-d` flag.

Adjust test_docker_integration to initial block no

Add project level dockerfile for dockerhub images

The intention is to have travis-ci build and push docker-images
- `on_success` (:develop) and
- `after_deploy` (:latest & :<tagged_version>)

hence this does not check out from git but uses the local source
directory.

[docker] Build docker image via travis-ci

This builds
- a new `hydrachain/hydrachain:develop` image after every
successful travis build
- a new `hydrachain/hydrachain:<version>` image after every
successful pypi deployment (will be tagged `:latest`, too.

Note: I hope this works right away -- it is kind of peculiar to test
ahead of time...

Add timeout parameter to wait_next_block

In some instances a waiting app instance lags 1 block behind the
network. Waiting indefinitely in such instances leads to deadlocks.

Now you can setup your `wait_next_block` function with a certain
timeout.
